                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/75.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                        General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-18T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>German Embassy transmits report that Constitutionalists have confiscated
                    warehouse and goods of German firm Eversbusch at Tampico, and that Germans are
                    subject to forced contributions.</p>
                <p>Stating that this is done at request of German Embassy, ask Carranza to order
                    restoration of Eversbusch’s property and that Germans be not subjected to forced
                    contributions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
